# UI RULES (shadcn + ViewState)

## Components

- Prefer shadcn/ui components (`frontend/src/components/ui/*`) over raw HTML controls.
- Keep styling consistent with Tailwind + Radix + shadcn patterns.

## ViewState

- Pages render by switching ViewState (e.g., idle/loading/submitting/success/error).
- UI should be “dumb”: render based on ViewState, no business logic.

## Shared status UI

- Put common states in shared UI:
  - `PageSkeleton`, `EmptyState`, `ErrorState`
- Error message must use a single normalization helper:
  - `toErrorMessage(err: unknown)` (no `any`)
